The dependence of F/F
                        0 and the concentration of the glucose within 0–2100 μM were represented in Fig. 7b. The plot does not fit a conventional linear Stern-Volmer equation which infers both static and dynamic quenching take place in the present sensor probe [70]. Inset of Fig. 7b revealed good linearity in the concentration range 0 to 210 μM and the linearly dependent coefficient R2 of 0.98795. The detection limit was calculated to be 1.7 μM using the three times standard deviation rule 3σ/s, where σ corresponds to the standard deviation of the blank sample and s refers to the slope of the calibration curve. These results were comparable to the studies reported previously (Table 2
                        ).
